      <hedline>
        <hl1>CANADA INFLATION INCREASES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Timothy Pritchard</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Pritchard, Timothy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Canada's annual inflation rate was 2.9 percent in June, up from 2.4 percent in May, and stronger than many economists expected; excluding energy, consumer prices advanced 1.4 percent in June (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Canada's annual inflation rate was 2.9 percent in June, up from 2.4 percent in May, and stronger than many economists had expected. Energy again supplied most of the cost pressure, with gasoline prices rising 6.3 percent in June, to stand 30.5 percent higher than a year earlier. Excluding energy, consumer prices advanced 1.4 percent in June.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard (NYT)</p>
      </block>
